title: Dead by Daylight - Official Stranger Things Welcome Back Trailer
description: The Stranger Things chapter returns to Dead by Daylight, bringing The Demogorgon back in The Fog as a Killer, with Nancy Wheeler and Steve Harrington back as Survivors in the multiplayer action/horror game. This chapter also features the Underground Complex map. Check out the latest trailer for Dead by Daylight to see what to expect with the Stranger Things chapter, and get ready to explore The Upside Down.

title: The Family Plan - Official Trailer (2023) Mark Wahlberg, Michelle Monaghan
description:
Check out the trailer for The Family Plan, an upcoming movie starring Mark Wahlberg, Michelle Monaghan, Zoe Colletti, Van Crosby, Saïd Taghmaoui, Maggie Q, and Ciarán Hinds.

Dan Morgan (Mark Wahlberg) loves his quiet suburban life as a devoted husband, father of three and successful car salesman. But that’s only half the story. Decades earlier, he was an elite government assassin tasked with eliminating the world’s deadliest threats. When enemies from his past track him down, Dan packs his unsuspecting wife (Michelle Monaghan), angsty teen daughter, pro-gamer teen son and adorable 10-month-old baby into their minivan and takes off on an impromptu cross-country road trip to Las Vegas. Determined to protect his family — while treating them to the vacation of a lifetime — Dan must put his long-dormant skills into action, without revealing his true identity.

The film is directed by Simon Cellan Jones and written by David Coggeshall. David Ellison, Dana Goldberg and Don Granger produce

title: Like a Dragon Gaiden: The Man Who Erased His Name - New Fighting Styles & Arena Modes
description:
From Kiryu’s Yakuza and Agent fighting styles to the offshore yakuza playground known as the Castle with no-holds-barred Coliseum clashes – here’s everything you need to know about kicking butt in Like a Dragon Gaiden: The Man Who Erased His Name. Presented by Like a Dragon Gaiden: The Man Who Erased His Name.
Kiryu's Yakuza style is characterized by its ferocious haymakers, bone-breaking kicks, and use of everyday objects as weapons. But Kiryu's new Agent style features powerful gadgets that would make any super spy envious! There's the lasso-like Spider gadget, jet boosting Serpent gadget, cigarette-shaped bomb known as the Firefly, and the Hornet -- an AI-powered combat drone.

Test all your new skills and toys in the Castle's Hell Arena in new game modes like the Hell Team Rumble.

title: Like a Dragon Gaiden: The Man Who Erased His Name Review
description:
Like a Dragon Gaiden: The Man Who Erased His Name reviewed by Tristan Ogilvie on Xbox Series X. Also available on Xbox One, PlayStation, and PC.

"Like a Dragon Gaiden: The Man Who Erased His Name is kind of like the cup of miso soup served before Infinite Wealth’s main course – it delivers an enjoyably familiar flavour that stimulates the appetite, but doesn’t really make for a substantial meal in its own right. It effectively feels like an appropriate lead-in to next year’s game in ways both good and bad – on the one hand, it gives a satisfying bit of back story to account for Kiryu’s presence in Hawaii, but on the other its uninspired substories and rehashed side activities are proof positive that the series is crying out for the seachange that Infinite Wealth looks to provide.
